# INSTRUCTIONS FOR NEW PROJECTS:
# 1. Rename this file from 'CODEOWNERS.example' to 'CODEOWNERS'.
# 2. Replace '@ProjectOwnerHandle' with the GitHub username or Team handle 
#    (e.g., @my-org/security-team) of the person/group responsible for this repository.
# 
# Purpose: Modifications to the files and directories listed below will require 
# explicit approval from the designated owners. This prevents unauthorized or 
# accidental bypassing of CI/CD pipelines, security scans, or community standards.

# Protect CI/CD pipelines and automation
/.github/workflows/             @ProjectOwnerHandle

# Protect GitHub templates and configuration
/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/        @ProjectOwnerHandle
/.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/ @ProjectOwnerHandle
/.github/CODEOWNERS             @ProjectOwnerHandle

# Protect community and security contracts
/CONTRIBUTING.md                @ProjectOwnerHandle
/SECURITY.md                    @ProjectOwnerHandle
/GOVERNANCE.md                  @ProjectOwnerHandle
